WEBVTT

00:06.574 --> 00:08.642
PREVIOUSLY ON
"UNITED STATES OF TARA"...

00:08.676 --> 00:10.378
Charmaine:
TARA, IS THERE ANY WAY...

00:10.411 --> 00:12.380
THAT I'D WATCH WHEELS?
HELLS YEAH.

00:12.413 --> 00:15.483
LOOK, MY BROTHER SAYS
THE SOONER I START,

00:15.516 --> 00:16.784
THE SOONER
I'LL BE BACK.

00:16.817 --> 00:18.652
JUST COME BACK TO US,
OKAY?

00:18.686 --> 00:19.753
I LIKED YOU.

00:21.789 --> 00:23.524
I LIKED YOU, TOO.

00:23.557 --> 00:25.493
YOU'RE STILL
IN LOVE WITH ME.

00:27.561 --> 00:29.263
YOUR SON GOT INTO
THE FILM FESTIVAL.

00:29.297 --> 00:30.531
WILL YOU TAKE ME?
TO NEW YORK?

00:30.564 --> 00:32.266
Marshall:
MAX MAKES GOOD.

00:32.300 --> 00:35.136
IS THAT REALLY WHAT YOU THINK
OF OUR FAMILY, OF ME?

00:35.169 --> 00:37.138
"MAX IS A COWARD
FOR HANGING IN THERE."

00:37.838 --> 00:39.407
OW! MONT--

00:39.440 --> 00:41.242
TIMEOUT!
TIME-FUCKING-OUT!

00:41.275 --> 00:43.777
WHY CAN'T WE LIVE
IN THE SAME CITY?

00:43.811 --> 00:46.780
AH, BECAUSE LIFE, MY DEAR,
IS NOT THAT NEAT.

00:46.814 --> 00:48.182
I MEAN, MY SISTER'S
A LITTLE LOOPY,

00:48.216 --> 00:49.550
YOU KNOW,
BUT SHE'S BETTER.

00:49.583 --> 00:51.452
I MEAN,
SHE SAYS SHE'S BETTER,

00:51.485 --> 00:53.221
SO I HAVE TO BELIEVE
SHE'S BETTER.
[ WHEELS CRIES ]

00:53.254 --> 00:54.222
AND WHO ARE YOU?

00:54.255 --> 00:55.823
I'M BRYCE CRAINE.

00:55.856 --> 00:57.791
[ VOMITS ]

01:03.331 --> 01:05.499
THIS IS SO GOOD, MOM.
I LOVE THE CRAB.

01:05.533 --> 01:07.435
[ COUGHS ]

01:07.468 --> 01:08.769
[ Strained ] EXTRAORDINARILY
ALLERGIC TO CRAB.

01:08.802 --> 01:09.770
I TOLD YOU THAT.

01:09.803 --> 01:11.672
CALL AN AMBULANCE!

01:12.740 --> 01:14.508
IT'S YOUR BIG BROTHER.

01:25.553 --> 01:28.189
WHY DID THEY PICK
SUCH AN EARLY FLIGHT?

01:28.222 --> 01:30.324
OH,
FREE SkyKans TICKET.

01:30.358 --> 01:32.260
ONE OF THE PERKS
OF SQUEEZING

01:32.293 --> 01:34.262
A LOW-BUDGET-AIRLINE HOSTESS
FROM MY LOINS.

01:34.295 --> 01:36.130
[ GROANS ]
SPEAKING OF LOINS,

01:36.164 --> 01:38.232
THANK GOD
NEIL COMES HOME TOMORROW.

01:38.266 --> 01:40.534
THIS IS THE LONGEST
I'VE GONE WITHOUT SEX,

01:40.568 --> 01:43.904
UNLESS YOU COUNT,
YOU KNOW, AGES ZERO TO 11.

01:43.937 --> 01:46.607
YOU LOST YOUR VIRGINITY
AT 11? WHO WITH?

01:46.640 --> 01:48.876
BENN BAINER,
OF THE BAINER BROTHERS.

01:48.909 --> 01:52.480
THE BROTHER WITH THE HARELIP?
HOW DID I NOT KNOW THIS?

01:52.513 --> 01:54.582
NO IDEA.
YOU WERE IN THE ROOM.

01:54.615 --> 01:56.384
HEY.

01:56.417 --> 01:58.619
OH.
DID YOU ASK HER?

01:58.652 --> 02:00.488
I WAS WAITING
FOR YOU.

02:00.521 --> 02:01.622
ASK ME WHAT?

02:01.655 --> 02:03.491
DID YOU TELL MAX
ABOUT BRYCE?

02:03.524 --> 02:04.925
NO.

02:04.958 --> 02:06.427
WHAT?
YOU DIDN'T TELL HIM?

02:06.460 --> 02:09.163
AND RUIN HIS BIG TRIP?
NO, MA'AM.

02:09.197 --> 02:11.532
TARA, YOU HAVE
A HOMICIDAL ALTER...

02:11.565 --> 02:14.168
WHO TRIED TO SEAFOOD
YOUR PROFESSOR.

02:14.202 --> 02:16.170
IT WAS A PRANK.
HE'S 14 YEARS OLD.

02:16.204 --> 02:18.306
HE DIDN'T UNDERSTAND
THE CONSEQUENCES.

02:18.339 --> 02:22.743
UH, AND ARE THESE, UM,
STAB WOUNDS FOR VENTILATION?

02:22.776 --> 02:25.213
TRUST ME.
I HAVE IT UNDER CONTROL.
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

02:25.246 --> 02:26.314
AND YOU ARE
SAYING THIS WHY?

02:30.751 --> 02:32.353
I THOUGHT HE WAS
BARFING UP YOUR PILLS.

02:32.386 --> 02:34.788
[ SNORTS ]

02:34.822 --> 02:37.891
OHHHH.
MOTHER, THERE ARE NO WORDS.

02:37.925 --> 02:40.861
OH, HONEY, IT'S TEMPORARY, JUST
UNTIL YOUR FATHER GETS HOME.

02:40.894 --> 02:42.796
AND THEN
HE AND I WILL MAKE A PLAN,

02:42.830 --> 02:44.365
AND WE WILL EXECUTE
SAID PLAN.

02:44.398 --> 02:45.866
[ SNIFFS ]

02:45.899 --> 02:47.935
AND IT WILL BE STAGGERINGLY
SUCCESSFUL, I PROMISE.

02:47.968 --> 02:50.471
BUT UNTIL THEN...

02:50.504 --> 02:52.606
THREE SNORTS A DAY
KEEPS THE PSYCHOS AWAY.

02:56.444 --> 02:57.678
Kate: UGH.

02:57.711 --> 02:59.213
Woman: HAVE A NICE DAY.
Man: THANK YOU.

02:59.247 --> 03:00.681
SO, DID YOU FIND
ANY TREASURES?

03:00.714 --> 03:02.383
I DON'T KNOW.

03:02.416 --> 03:05.453
DOES A SUCKED-ON JOLLY RANCHER
STUCK TO A TRAY TABLE COUNT?

03:05.486 --> 03:06.554
YES, IT DOES.

03:06.587 --> 03:08.689
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

03:08.722 --> 03:09.823
MM.

03:09.857 --> 03:11.325
MMM!

03:11.359 --> 03:13.261
WHAT IS THAT --
CHOCOLATE AND COCONUT?

03:13.294 --> 03:15.429
SkyKans'
SIGNATURE DISINFECTANT.

03:15.463 --> 03:16.730
OOH. HOW DECADENT.

03:16.764 --> 03:18.866
[ CHUCKLES ]
I THINK THAT I'M TASTIER

03:18.899 --> 03:20.901
WHEN I'M NOT CHASED
WITH A SHOT OF FERAL 8-YEAR-OLD.

03:20.934 --> 03:22.736
UH, YEAH,
THAT IS NOT IDEAL. SORRY.

03:22.770 --> 03:24.972
CORRINE AND I ARE STILL TRYING
TO FIGURE OUT OUR SCHEDULES.

03:25.005 --> 03:26.407
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

03:26.440 --> 03:27.741
I THINK
THAT MY DOMESTIC SITUATION

03:27.775 --> 03:30.578
HAS YOURS BEAT
BY LIKE A GAZILLION.

03:30.611 --> 03:32.413
INTRIGUING. CONTINUE.

03:32.446 --> 03:35.783
OKAY. SUNDAY DINNER
AT THE GREGSON HOUSE.

03:35.816 --> 03:38.486
MY MOM ASSUMES THE IDENTITY
OF HER MOLESTY STEPBROTHER

03:38.519 --> 03:40.454
TO NEARLY COMMIT MURDER
BY SHELLFISH.

03:40.488 --> 03:42.323
THE VICTIM --
HER PSYCH PROFESSOR,

03:42.356 --> 03:44.725
WHO IS DEATHLY ALLERGIC TO CRAB,
WHICH SHE KNEW ABOUT.

03:44.758 --> 03:45.826
UM...

03:45.859 --> 03:47.595
MY MOM BECOMES
DIFFERENT PEOPLE

03:47.628 --> 03:50.264
TO COPE WITH THE SHIT
THAT OTHER PEOPLE DO YOGA FOR.

03:50.298 --> 03:53.767
IT'S SOME CHILDHOOD TRAUMA
DEALING WITH HER DAD'S SON,

03:53.801 --> 03:57.471
WHO DID SOMETHING TO HER
IN A CORNFIELD, OR...

03:57.505 --> 04:01.309
WAIT. IS THIS --
I-I-IS THIS TOO MUCH?

04:01.342 --> 04:02.943
N-NO.
HMM?

04:02.976 --> 04:04.312
UH, YEAH.

04:04.345 --> 04:05.913
UM, IT'S, UH,
A LITTLE BIT --

04:05.946 --> 04:08.316
I MEAN, IT'S JUST A LOT --
AND QUICK.

04:08.349 --> 04:09.317
BUT...

04:09.350 --> 04:11.519
GOOD...

04:11.552 --> 04:12.786
ULTIMATELY.

04:12.820 --> 04:14.888
UM, WHERE --
WHERE SHOULD WE GO?

04:14.922 --> 04:17.024
UH, TO STARBUCKS
OR QUIZNOS?

04:17.057 --> 04:19.026
Marshall:
THE WORLD SEEMS SO SMALL NOW.

04:19.059 --> 04:20.794
THE ENTIRE WORLD
SEEMS SMALLER?

04:20.828 --> 04:22.463
COMPARED TO NEW YORK.

04:22.496 --> 04:24.365
THAT SOFA IS 3 INCHES SHORTER
THAN WHEN I LEFT.

04:24.398 --> 04:25.466
LOOK AT THAT.

04:25.499 --> 04:26.834
IN NEW YORK
FOR FIVE DAYS,

04:26.867 --> 04:28.602
AND MARSHALL'S SUDDENLY
MR. NEW YORK.

04:28.636 --> 04:30.338
HE'S LIKE
A REGULAR WOODY ALLEN.

04:30.371 --> 04:32.606
THE ONLY NEW YORKER
THAT DAD SEEMS TO KNOW.

04:32.640 --> 04:34.007
WE SAW HIM
EVERYWHERE WE WENT.

04:34.041 --> 04:36.644
APPARENTLY,
WOODY ALLEN WORKS THE REGISTER

04:36.677 --> 04:38.646
AT FAO SCHWARZ
ON FIFTH AVE.

04:38.679 --> 04:41.649
A LOT OF PEOPLE LOOK ALIKE
IN THIS WORLD.

04:41.682 --> 04:43.917
I'VE GOT TO GO
TO SCHOOL.

04:43.951 --> 04:45.586
YOU TWO ALL RIGHT?

04:45.619 --> 04:49.723
YEAH, YEAH.
IT'S -- IT'S COMPLICATED.

04:49.757 --> 04:51.925
I'M PROUD OF HIM,
BUT WE, UH...

04:51.959 --> 04:54.662
WE GOT A LITTLE --
WE GOT A LITTLE RAW.

04:54.695 --> 04:56.764
I'LL -- I'LL TELL YOU
ABOUT IT LATER.

04:56.797 --> 04:58.866
I-I SORT OF
NEED TO TALK NOW.

04:58.899 --> 05:01.335
BAD STUFF? BIG STUFF?

05:01.369 --> 05:03.571
UH...YES.

05:03.604 --> 05:05.773
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

05:05.806 --> 05:08.075
NEW ALTER.

05:08.108 --> 05:10.077
OH, BUT PLEASE
DON'T MAKE THAT FACE.

05:10.110 --> 05:12.413
UH, I HAVE IT
UNDER CONTROL.

05:12.446 --> 05:13.981
I'M ALLOWED TO HAVE
ANY LOOK I WANT.

05:14.014 --> 05:15.749
YOU KNOW
I'D HAVE COME HOME EARLIER.

05:15.783 --> 05:18.786
[ Sighing ]
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

05:18.819 --> 05:20.688
WHO IS SHE?
GOOD? BAD ALTER?

05:20.721 --> 05:23.757
LOVES GIVING BACK MASSAGE
AND KNOWS THE STOCK MARKET?

05:23.791 --> 05:26.360
NO? NO? WE'RE NEVER GONNA HAVE
ONE OF THOSE, ARE WE?

05:26.394 --> 05:27.895
[ SIGHS ]

05:27.928 --> 05:31.599
HE IS 14 YEARS OLD...

05:31.632 --> 05:33.967
AND HIS NAME IS...BRYCE.

05:34.001 --> 05:35.736
ARE YOU --

05:35.769 --> 05:36.837
BRYCE?!

05:36.870 --> 05:38.706
AS IN BRYCE BRYCE?!

05:38.739 --> 05:40.374
I'M MEDICATED --
HEAVILY MEDICATED.

05:40.408 --> 05:41.909
I HAVE IT
COMPLETELY UNDER CONTROL.

05:41.942 --> 05:44.077
Marshall: DAD, LET'S GO!
WE'RE GONNA BE LATE!

05:44.111 --> 05:46.079
OKAY. WE'RE NOT DONE.

05:47.548 --> 05:49.850
OKAY.

05:49.883 --> 05:53.053
LOOK WHAT I GOT --
CHARMAINE'S FAMOUS HOT COCOA

05:53.086 --> 05:55.456
WITH RUM SHOTS
AND LUCKY CHARMS.

05:55.489 --> 05:57.157
WITH JUST
THE HORSESHOES!

05:57.190 --> 05:58.859
TAKE OFF YOUR JACKET.
YOU'RE HOME.

05:58.892 --> 06:00.060
MWAH.

06:00.093 --> 06:01.729
I DON'T WANT
TO PUT HER DOWN.

06:01.762 --> 06:03.997
MY ARMS HAVE BEEN ITCHING
THESE LAST FEW WEEKS.

06:04.031 --> 06:06.934
JUST BEEN ACHING FOR HER --
ACHING FOR HER.

06:06.967 --> 06:08.436
WHAT'S SHE DOING?

06:08.469 --> 06:09.937
IS SHE -- SHE LAUGHING,
SHE DROOLING,

06:09.970 --> 06:11.605
SHE --
SHE ROLLING JOINTS?

06:11.639 --> 06:12.940
[ LAUGHS ]

06:12.973 --> 06:14.542
SHE'S GOT
THREE NEW FACIAL EXPRESSIONS.

06:14.575 --> 06:15.743
OH.

06:15.776 --> 06:17.711
THIS ONE
WHEN SHE'S POOPING.

06:17.745 --> 06:20.581
[ LAUGHS ]
"CONSTIPATED GERIATRIC." NICE.

06:20.614 --> 06:23.617
UM, THIS ONE.

06:23.651 --> 06:24.952
"ELEVATOR FART SNIFFER."

06:24.985 --> 06:26.887
AND...

06:26.920 --> 06:29.823
[ Laughing ] OH!
"ROLLER-COASTER DOUCHE BAG"!

06:29.857 --> 06:31.892
OH,
YOU'RE SO TALENTED!

06:36.564 --> 06:39.166
[ SNORTS ]

06:39.199 --> 06:40.434
[ SNIFFS ]

06:40.468 --> 06:42.402
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

06:45.005 --> 06:48.175
BEING BORN IN NEW YORK DOES NOT
MAKE YOU ANY MORE SPECIAL.

06:48.208 --> 06:51.645
IT'S LUCK.
THEIR MOVIES WERE JUST OKAY.

06:51.679 --> 06:53.747
THEY'RE NOT MAGIC GENIUSES
BECAUSE THEY LIVE

06:53.781 --> 06:55.849
ON THE UPPER WEST SIDE
AND DRINK EGG CREAMS.

06:55.883 --> 06:58.519
EGGS AND CREAM?
THAT'S A THING?

06:58.552 --> 07:00.788
THAT SOUNDS LIKE
VOMIT JUICE.

07:00.821 --> 07:03.857
WELL, HOW DO YOU ALL FEEL
ABOUT SOUVENIRS?

07:03.891 --> 07:04.858
PRO OR CON?

07:04.892 --> 07:06.193
PRO, DEFINITELY.

07:06.226 --> 07:08.696
We lost one of our students
last night.

07:08.729 --> 07:10.531
REALLY? WHICH ONE?

07:10.564 --> 07:13.233
FYI -- I WON'T BE ABLE
TO FIT A T-SHIRT OVER MY HEAD

07:13.266 --> 07:15.168
FOR THE NEXT TWO MONTHS.

07:15.202 --> 07:17.938
I ASSUME THEY DIDN'T HAVE ANY
"I HEART NEW YORK" BUTTON-UPS?

07:17.971 --> 07:19.573
I THINK YOU SHOULD
TELL THEM, ALBERT.

07:19.607 --> 07:22.943
EMOTIONAL CHILDREN
MAKE ME VERY UNCOMFORTABLE.

07:22.976 --> 07:24.812
SO...

07:24.845 --> 07:26.914
ALL RIGHT, CLASS.
UH, EYES HERE, EARS OPEN.

07:26.947 --> 07:28.649
I HAVE SOME NEWS.

07:28.682 --> 07:30.918
IT'S NOT THE KIND OF NEWS
ANYBODY LIKES TO GET.

07:30.951 --> 07:32.920
YOU KNOW, WHEN I WAS 16,

07:32.953 --> 07:35.188
UH, THERE WERE
A LOT OF TRACTOR ACCIDENTS,

07:35.222 --> 07:37.991
AND, UH, DONNY CHAMPLAIN
WAS THE QUARTERBACK.

07:38.025 --> 07:39.593
NOW, WE ALL
CALLED HIM "PEACHES"

07:39.627 --> 07:41.128
'CAUSE, UH,
HE HAD A-A PEACH TREE --

07:41.161 --> 07:42.696
LIONEL TRANE'S DEAD.

07:42.730 --> 07:44.698
[ STUDENTS MURMUR ]

07:44.732 --> 07:47.535
IT WAS A CAR ACCIDENT --
LAST NIGHT.

07:55.543 --> 07:58.178
[ SIGHS ]

07:58.211 --> 08:00.280
HE DIDN'T SAY A WORD
THE ENTIRE RIDE.

08:00.313 --> 08:03.216
[ Drowsily ]
OH, MY POOR BOY.

08:03.250 --> 08:05.586
THIS IS WHAT YOU MEANT
BY "MEDICATED"?

08:05.619 --> 08:08.722
IF YOU HAD A MUSTACHE,
YOU'D LOOK JUST LIKE STALIN.

08:08.756 --> 08:09.757
Marshall: NOW WHAT?

08:09.790 --> 08:11.191
UH, SHE'LL BE FINE.

08:11.224 --> 08:13.026
SHE HAD TO UP HER MEDS.
YOU GET IT.

08:13.060 --> 08:15.696
OF COURSE. WOULDN'T BE HER
IF IT WASN'T SOMETHING, RIGHT?

08:15.729 --> 08:18.532
[ GROANS ] THERE'S ALWAYS
SOMETHING, MOOSHOO,

08:18.566 --> 08:20.100
[ Laughing ]
LIKE A CHINESE PANCAKE.

08:20.133 --> 08:21.869
IT DOESN'T MATTER.
IT REALLY DOESN'T.

08:21.902 --> 08:24.271
I GET HER OR I GET ALICE
AND A PEACH COBBLER.

08:24.304 --> 08:25.939
WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?

08:27.040 --> 08:28.275
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

08:28.308 --> 08:29.943
I CANNOT BELIEVE
I GOT HERE SO FAST.

08:29.977 --> 08:31.579
PLANE TO CAR.
SPEEDING LIKE A BLUR.

08:31.612 --> 08:33.280
I JUST -- I HEARD
WHAT HAPPENED TO MARSHALL,

08:33.313 --> 08:35.115
AND I JUST HAD TO BE HERE,
YOU KNOW?

08:35.148 --> 08:36.116
WHAT DO YOU NEED?

08:36.149 --> 08:37.885
[ DOORKNOB RATTLES ]

08:37.918 --> 08:39.853
HE LOCKED THE DOOR.
I JUST WANT TO SEE IF HE'S OKAY.

08:39.887 --> 08:41.154
COME ON, MARSH.

08:41.188 --> 08:42.623
OH, WELL, DO YOU WANT TO KNOW
WHAT TO SAY,

08:42.656 --> 08:43.891
OR DO YOU WANT
TO BREAK IN THERE?

08:43.924 --> 08:45.258
BECAUSE I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO SAY,

08:45.292 --> 08:47.227
BUT I CAN BREAK INTO
ANY LOCKED DOOR IN THIS HOUSE.

08:47.260 --> 08:49.229
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

08:49.262 --> 08:50.798
TOOK YOU LONG ENOUGH.

08:53.767 --> 08:56.303
WELL, BUDDY,
YOU COULD HAVE OPENED THE DOOR

08:56.336 --> 08:57.871
AND SAVED US SOME TIME.

08:57.905 --> 09:00.007
THAT'S NOT
WHY PEOPLE LOCK DOORS.

09:02.375 --> 09:04.945
I DON'T HAVE TO
GO TO WORK...

09:04.978 --> 09:07.180
IF YOU WANT ME
TO HANG AROUND.

09:07.214 --> 09:08.682
PLEASE GO TO WORK.

09:08.716 --> 09:10.818
DON'T DO
ANYTHING DIFFERENT FOR ME.

09:12.786 --> 09:16.056
I'M REALLY SORRY
ABOUT LIONEL, MOOSH.

09:16.089 --> 09:19.693
HE'LL ALWAYS BE
MY SECOND-BEST GAY.

09:19.727 --> 09:21.795
[ Singsong voice ] BECAUSE
YOU'RE MY FIRST-BEST GAY.

09:21.829 --> 09:23.931
NO?

09:23.964 --> 09:26.667
YOU REALLY
WANT ME TO GO?

09:26.700 --> 09:28.268
OKAY.

09:28.301 --> 09:31.772
I'LL BE OVER THERE
OR NEXT DOOR -- CLOSE.

09:34.675 --> 09:37.978
* OH, WE'RE GONNA CHANGE
YOUR LITTLE DIAP-DIAP *

09:38.011 --> 09:38.979
HEY.

09:39.012 --> 09:39.980
HI!

09:40.013 --> 09:41.381
WHAT'S WITH THE MASK?

09:41.414 --> 09:42.916
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:42.950 --> 09:46.386
FOUND I LOST THE ABILITY
TO STAND THE STENCH.

09:46.419 --> 09:48.188
I DON'T WANT TO PUKE
ON THE BABY.

09:48.221 --> 09:49.156
SCALPEL.

09:51.124 --> 09:53.026
OH, YEAH.

09:53.060 --> 09:56.930
SO, WHAT'S WITH THE NEW DUDE
INSIDE OF TARA?

09:56.964 --> 09:58.966
OH...

09:58.999 --> 10:00.968
ANY OTHER TIME,
WE'D BE SCRAMBLING AROUND

10:01.001 --> 10:03.236
LIKE RABID GERBILS
AROUND HER,

10:03.270 --> 10:05.706
BUT WE'RE FOCUSING
ON MARSHALL RIGHT NOW

10:05.739 --> 10:08.341
'CAUSE HE'S NOT DOING
TOO GOOD.

10:10.010 --> 10:13.346
WE MAKE
THESE TINY, PERFECT CREATURES,

10:13.380 --> 10:16.316
PROMISE THEM
NOTHING'S GONNA HURT THEM,

10:16.349 --> 10:17.384
PROMISE OURSELVES.

10:17.417 --> 10:19.119
YEAH.

10:19.152 --> 10:22.089
AND THEN THE WORLD JUST UNLOADS
A SHITSTORM IN THEIR FACES.

10:22.122 --> 10:23.090
HM.

10:23.123 --> 10:26.193
AND YOU REALIZE...

10:26.226 --> 10:27.928
NOTHING'S
IN YOUR CONTROL.

10:27.961 --> 10:30.363
YEAH, WELL, YOU CAN'T FIX IT,
MAN, YOU KNOW?

10:30.397 --> 10:33.967
YOU JUST GOT TO BE THERE
FOR HIM, HOPE YOU'RE CAPABLE.

10:34.001 --> 10:35.135
FORCEPS.

10:35.168 --> 10:36.136
AAAAH!

10:36.169 --> 10:38.138
OH, GOD.
AAH. OKAY.

10:38.171 --> 10:39.239
DUDE...

10:39.272 --> 10:40.674
I-I KNOW.
I KNOW, I KNOW.

10:43.176 --> 10:44.778
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

10:44.812 --> 10:46.379
UH, JUST A SECOND.

10:46.413 --> 10:49.683
Max: HEY, HONEY,
SHOULD I WEAR MY CHARCOAL SUIT

10:49.717 --> 10:51.985
OR THE BLACK ONE
TOMORROW?

10:53.987 --> 10:55.923
TOO BAD
YOU DON'T HAVE FUCHSIA.

10:55.956 --> 10:57.290
[ Chuckling ] YEAH.

10:57.324 --> 10:59.226
HEY, HONEY, IF YOU'RE
FEELING ANY BETTER,

10:59.259 --> 11:01.995
MAYBE YOU CAN GO CHECK
ON MARSHALL, TOO, OKAY?

11:09.469 --> 11:11.404
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

11:14.942 --> 11:17.077
IS IT OKAY
IF I COME IN?

11:19.046 --> 11:21.014
IT'S YOUR HOUSE.

11:21.048 --> 11:23.150
THE DOORS
ARE MERELY SUGGESTIONS.

11:28.455 --> 11:32.192
I, UH...

11:32.225 --> 11:36.196
I FOUND THIS PICTURE
OF YOU GUYS THIS SUMMER.

11:36.229 --> 11:38.065
REMEMBER,
THEY WERE SHOWING MOVIES

11:38.098 --> 11:39.466
ON THE WALL
AT THE LIBRARY?

11:46.106 --> 11:48.809
WE GOT INTO A FIGHT
RIGHT AFTER THAT.

11:48.842 --> 11:50.210
YEAH.

11:50.243 --> 11:54.081
BUT THEN IT WAS OVER,
AND WE GOT ICE CREAM.

11:56.183 --> 11:58.351
AND I WATCHED HIM
WATCHING YOU.

11:58.385 --> 12:02.890
THAT'S THE KIND OF THING
A MOTHER RARELY GETS TO DO --

12:02.923 --> 12:07.795
WATCH SOMEONE WATCH YOUR KID
AND SEE THE SAME THING YOU DO.

12:07.828 --> 12:10.964
WE WERE TERRIBLE
TOGETHER.

12:10.998 --> 12:12.532
YOU KNOW THAT.

12:12.565 --> 12:14.434
WE WEREN'T IN LOVE.

12:14.467 --> 12:18.071
WELL, YOU WEREN'T
SOUL MATES, BUT...

12:18.105 --> 12:20.874
I THINK HE STILL
WANTED TO WATCH YOU,

12:20.908 --> 12:23.210
SEE WHAT
YOU WERE GONNA DO NEXT.

12:26.980 --> 12:30.951
TOMORROW,
IT WON'T BE LIKE THIS.

12:32.385 --> 12:34.354
I'M -- I'M HERE,
HOWEVER YOU NEED ME.

12:34.387 --> 12:36.256
I'LL STAY HERE
FOR THE FUNERAL,

12:36.289 --> 12:38.826
OR...I'LL BE THERE
WITH YOU.

12:38.859 --> 12:40.994
IT'S -- IT'S YOUR CALL.

12:41.028 --> 12:43.797
HEY, UM...

12:46.166 --> 12:47.835
PLEASE COME.

12:49.569 --> 12:50.971
YEAH.

12:58.178 --> 13:00.814
[ KNOCK ON DOOR TO
"SHAVE AND A HAIRCUT" RHYTHM ]

13:00.848 --> 13:02.782
[ KNOCKS TWICE ]

13:08.989 --> 13:12.860
HEY, UM, LOOK, I-I FEEL LIKE
I SHOULD JUST APOLOGIZE,

13:12.893 --> 13:15.829
UM, FOR SHOVING MY HYPERACTIVE
SPAWN DOWN YOUR THROAT.

13:15.863 --> 13:20.300
HE'S JUST...YOU KNOW, UM...
PART OF THE PACKAGE.

13:20.333 --> 13:22.169
A-A-AND I DON'T MEAN
THAT I'M, LIKE, A PACKAGE.

13:22.202 --> 13:23.436
IT'S NOT LIKE I WASN'T

13:23.470 --> 13:25.038
HEMORRHAGING
MY OWN FAMILY BULLSHIT.

13:25.072 --> 13:27.841
I DON'T WANT
TO BOG YOU DOWN.

13:27.875 --> 13:29.476
YEAH, BECAUSE, I MEAN,
WE BOTH HAVE, LIKE,

13:29.509 --> 13:30.978
A TON OF STUFF
GOING ON RIGHT NOW.

13:31.011 --> 13:33.013
YEAH. WE SHOULD JUST
KEEP IT SUPER-CASUAL.

13:33.046 --> 13:37.150
I AM SO GLAD
THAT YOU SAID THAT.

13:37.184 --> 13:38.618
MM.
AND DOES "SUPER-CASUAL" --

13:38.651 --> 13:43.924
THAT MEANS THAT WE'RE LIKE
KHAKIS OR...JEAN SHORTS?

13:43.957 --> 13:46.860
WELL, LIKE -- LIKE,
THOSE WEIRD CALF-LENGTH SHORTS

13:46.894 --> 13:48.195
THAT KEVIN SMITH WEARS?

13:48.228 --> 13:49.863
"JORTS."

13:49.897 --> 13:52.032
YEAH. WE'RE JORTS.

13:54.101 --> 13:57.204
MM. BUT...SO -- SO JUST,
MORE CASUAL THAN WE ARE NOW?

13:57.237 --> 13:58.471
MM-HMM.

13:58.505 --> 14:00.573
SO, DO YOU WANT TO...
DATE OTHER PEOPLE?

14:00.607 --> 14:02.475
NO WAY.

14:02.509 --> 14:04.077
WHOA. WAIT. DID YOU?

14:04.111 --> 14:06.179
NO. NO.

14:06.213 --> 14:08.015
OKAY.
NO.

14:08.048 --> 14:10.217
BUT IF WE'RE JORTS, THAT MEANS
THAT WE'RE, LIKE, NOT PANTS.

14:10.250 --> 14:11.952
MM.

14:11.985 --> 14:13.620
AND IF WE'RE NOT PANTS
AND WE'RE NOT SHORTS,

14:13.653 --> 14:15.322
THEN WE'RE...

14:15.355 --> 14:17.390
NOT ANYTHING.

14:19.359 --> 14:20.928
RIGHT.

14:22.662 --> 14:25.265
WELL, I'M GLAD
THAT WE FIGURED THIS OUT.

14:27.100 --> 14:29.169
ME TOO.

14:30.670 --> 14:32.172
OKAY.

14:35.976 --> 14:38.011
[ SIGHS ]

14:38.045 --> 14:39.379
[ GROANS ]

14:41.949 --> 14:45.518
LIFE IS
SO FUCKING FRAGILE.

14:45.552 --> 14:46.653
[ SIGHS ]

14:46.686 --> 14:48.288
YOU KNOW
WHAT I KEEP THINKING?

14:48.321 --> 14:49.656
HMM?

14:49.689 --> 14:52.059
IT COULD HAVE BEEN HIM
IN THE CAR.

14:52.092 --> 14:53.560
OH, BABY...
I KNOW.

14:53.593 --> 14:56.363
DON'T -- DON'T GO THERE.
I CAN'T HELP IT.

14:56.396 --> 15:01.668
WE GOT TO...
NOT TAKE SHIT FOR GRANTED,

15:01.701 --> 15:05.638
APPRECIATE EVERYTHING WE GOT,
WHICH IS A BOATLOAD.

15:05.672 --> 15:07.174
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

15:07.207 --> 15:09.709
I FEEL LIKE MY WHOLE LIFE
IS BOILING DOWN

15:09.742 --> 15:13.380
TO THIS ONE FUCKING
BLIP IN TIME.

15:13.413 --> 15:15.382
IF I CAN'T MOTHER THAT BOY
RIGHT NOW,

15:15.415 --> 15:18.551
WHEN HE NEEDS ME
THE MOST...

15:18.585 --> 15:20.320
WHAT AM I?

15:22.055 --> 15:24.291
Max: SAYS HERE
THE FUNERAL'S AT NOON

15:24.324 --> 15:26.559
AND WE ALL DRIVE
OVER TO THE CEMETERY.

15:26.593 --> 15:28.028
IS MOOSH GONNA SPEAK?

15:28.061 --> 15:29.296
I DON'T KNOW, HONEY.

15:29.329 --> 15:32.132
THIS FUCKING SUCKS.
I HATE FUNERALS.

15:32.165 --> 15:33.466
REALLY?

15:33.500 --> 15:36.403
MOST PEOPLE LOVE
MOURNING VIOLENT DEATH.

15:36.436 --> 15:39.006
IS THIS AN OPEN-CASKET
FUNERAL OR WHAT?

15:39.039 --> 15:41.341
WELL, JUDGING
FROM THE ACCIDENT REPORT,

15:41.374 --> 15:43.643
I DOUBT
HE'S IN ANY SHAPE FOR THAT.

15:43.676 --> 15:45.612
HEY, MOOSHY.

15:47.247 --> 15:49.416
Ted:
HOW YOU DOING, KIDDO?

15:50.683 --> 15:52.185
I UNDERSTAND.

15:52.219 --> 15:54.187
WHEN I LOST
MY DEAR MOTHER,

15:54.221 --> 15:56.689
I DIDN'T SPEAK
TO ANYONE FOR MONTHS.

15:56.723 --> 15:58.625
OF COURSE,
WE WERE CLOSER THAN MOST.

15:58.658 --> 16:00.427
I-I BRUSHED HER HAIR
EVERY DAY,

16:00.460 --> 16:03.163
AND WE SLEPT
IN THE SAME BED --

16:03.196 --> 16:04.164
UH, HEY, TED...

16:04.197 --> 16:05.432
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
TARA!

16:05.465 --> 16:07.234
WE, UH, WE WANT
TO GET THERE EARLY.

16:07.267 --> 16:09.402
YOU ABOUT READY?

16:13.573 --> 16:15.475
MOM?

16:15.508 --> 16:17.610
[ As Bryce ]
MORNING, FOLKS.

16:17.644 --> 16:19.679
AND HELLO AGAIN,
CHARMAINE.

16:21.514 --> 16:22.749
KATHERINE.

16:24.684 --> 16:28.088
MY APOLOGIES FOR MY POOR
TABLE MANNERS THE OTHER NIGHT.

16:28.121 --> 16:30.157
AWFULLY IMPOLITE OF ME.

16:30.190 --> 16:32.225
TARA'S MIFFED
SHE CAN'T BE HERE TODAY,

16:32.259 --> 16:35.062
THOUGH SHE SENDS HER BEST
FROM CABO.

16:35.095 --> 16:36.496
[ LAUGHS ]

16:36.529 --> 16:39.599
HAVE A GREAT DAY,
TARA'S FAMILY.

16:39.632 --> 16:43.136
GO PUT THE "FUN"
BACK IN "FUNERAL."

16:50.110 --> 16:51.378
LET'S GO.

16:51.411 --> 16:52.779
[ BLACK FLAG'S "SPRAY PAINT"
PLAYS ]

16:52.812 --> 16:54.581
* IT FEELS GOOD
TO SAY WHAT I WANT *

16:54.614 --> 16:56.383
* IT FEELS GOOD
TO KNOCK THINGS DOWN *

16:56.416 --> 16:58.318
* IT FEELS GOOD TO SEE
THE DISGUST IN THEIR EYES *

16:58.351 --> 17:00.453
* IT FEELS GOOD,
I'M GONNA GO WILD *

17:00.487 --> 17:02.289
* SPRAY PAINT THE WALLS

17:02.322 --> 17:04.191
* I DON'T WANT
TO SEE THE PLAN SUCCEED *

17:04.224 --> 17:05.525
* THERE WON'T BE ROOM
FOR PEOPLE LIKE ME *

17:05.558 --> 17:07.327
* MY LIFE IS THEIR DISEASE

17:07.360 --> 17:09.396
* IT FEELS GOOD,
I'M GONNA GO WILD *

17:09.429 --> 17:11.598
* SPRAY PAINT THE WALLS

17:11.631 --> 17:13.266
* IT FEELS GOOD
TO SAY WHAT I WANT *

17:13.300 --> 17:15.068
* FEELS SO GOOD
TO KNOCK THINGS DOWN *

17:15.102 --> 17:16.636
* IT FEELS GOOD TO SEE
THE DISGUST IN THEIR EYES *

17:16.669 --> 17:18.805
* IT FEELS GOOD,
I'M GONNA GO WILD *

17:18.838 --> 17:20.673
* SPRAY PAINT THE WALLS

17:20.707 --> 17:23.276
* SPRAY PAINT THE WALLS

17:23.310 --> 17:24.777
* IT FEELS GOOD,
I'M GONNA GO WILD *

17:24.811 --> 17:27.614
I THOUGHT
IT WAS NICE.

17:27.647 --> 17:29.582
I GUESS IT'S WEIRD
TO CALL A FUNERAL "NICE,"

17:29.616 --> 17:30.650
BUT IT WAS DIFFERENT.

17:30.683 --> 17:31.651
WHAT'S THE WORD?

17:31.684 --> 17:32.652
FLAMBOYANT.

17:32.685 --> 17:34.221
IT WAS TASTEFUL.

17:34.254 --> 17:36.156
IT WAS FLAMBOYANT.

17:36.189 --> 17:39.292
WHEN I GO, I HOPE
THAT MY PARENTS COULD SEE ME

17:39.326 --> 17:42.495
AS GAY AND AT PEACE
IN A ROOMFUL OF FRIENDS.

17:42.529 --> 17:45.398
LIONEL TRANE ALWAYS SAID
EXACTLY WHAT WAS ON HIS MIND,

17:45.432 --> 17:46.566
AND I RESPECT THAT.

17:46.599 --> 17:47.834
YOU KNOW WHAT HE SAID
TO ME ONCE?

17:47.867 --> 17:51.171
HE SAID, "KATE,
LEGGINGS ARE NOT PANTS."

17:51.204 --> 17:53.506
AND HE WAS RIGHT.

17:53.540 --> 17:55.708
DID YOU SEE
THE NEWSPAPER?

17:55.742 --> 17:57.177
WHAT'S THAT,
BUDDY?

17:57.210 --> 18:00.180
WELL, UM,
LOOK AT THE HEADLINE.

18:00.213 --> 18:04.317
IT SAYS "LOCAL STUDENT TRANE
KILLED IN CRASH."

18:04.351 --> 18:06.186
IF YOU DIDN'T READ THE ARTICLE,
YOU'D THINK

18:06.219 --> 18:09.189
THAT A LOCAL TRAIN FULL OF
STUDENTS WERE KILLED IN A CRASH.

18:09.222 --> 18:11.258
LIKE, IF HE DIED
SLIGHTLY DIFFERENTLY,

18:11.291 --> 18:12.859
THEY'D HAVE
A BETTER HEADLINE.

18:12.892 --> 18:15.328
YEAH, IT'S KIND OF LIKE
THE WRITER WAS THINKING,

18:15.362 --> 18:17.664
"I JUST WISH HE WOULD HAVE DIED
A LITTLE BIT FUNNIER."

18:17.697 --> 18:18.665
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:20.333 --> 18:23.736
"TRANE TRAINS TRAIN,
TRAGICALLY."

18:23.770 --> 18:25.605
"DIES."
* WAH-WAH

18:25.638 --> 18:26.739
[ LAUGHTER ]

18:26.773 --> 18:28.608
OKAY, UM...

18:28.641 --> 18:32.745
HE...CRASHED INTO A TRAIN
AT HIS OWN FAMILY REUNION.

18:32.779 --> 18:35.748
"TRANE SMASH INTO TRAIN CRASH
AT TRANE BASH."

18:35.782 --> 18:37.750
[ LAUGHTER ]

18:37.784 --> 18:39.686
WAIT.
I WANT TO DO ONE.

18:39.719 --> 18:41.388
"LIONEL..."

18:43.423 --> 18:46.626
FUCK!
I'M SO BAD AT WORD GAMES!

18:46.659 --> 18:48.228
GUYS, PLEASE.

18:48.261 --> 18:50.363
I CAN HEAR YOUR SOPPY BULLSHIT
FROM UPSTAIRS.

18:50.397 --> 18:52.565
HOW DOES A GUY WHACK OFF
IN PEACE IN THIS HOUSE?

18:52.599 --> 18:53.533
FUCKING, REALLY.

18:55.335 --> 18:56.769
KIDDING, OF COURSE.

18:56.803 --> 18:58.771
I ALWAYS FIND A WAY
TO WHACK IT.

18:58.805 --> 19:01.874
KATE, FYI --
YOUR PINK TEDDY BEAR AND I

19:01.908 --> 19:05.445
SHARED A WONDERFUL
MOMENT IN TIME.

19:05.478 --> 19:08.648
OH, AND I FOUND THIS LETTER
IN MARSH'S ROOM.

19:08.681 --> 19:10.483
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

19:10.517 --> 19:15.222
"MARSHALL, WE ARE STARS.

19:15.255 --> 19:17.390
"WE WILL GET BRIGHTER,

19:17.424 --> 19:20.293
AND WE WILL SHINE
FOREVER AND EVER."

19:20.327 --> 19:22.262
[ LAUGHS ]

19:22.295 --> 19:26.399
IT'S FUNNY 'CAUSE IT'S RETARDED
AND HE'S DEAD.

19:26.433 --> 19:28.735
LEAVE HIM ALONE,
MOM.

19:28.768 --> 19:30.603
Marshall:
SHE'S NOT IN THERE.

19:30.637 --> 19:32.272
BUT SHE LET THIS HAPPEN,

19:32.305 --> 19:34.874
BECAUSE NO ONE CAN HAVE
BIGGER PROBLEMS THAN HER, RIGHT?

19:34.907 --> 19:37.244
OH, TARA'S
THE FUCKING WORST, HUH?

19:37.277 --> 19:38.845
ALL RIGHT,
IT'S BEEN FUN, BRYCE,

19:38.878 --> 19:40.813
BUT THIS THING HAS A CLOCK
ON IT. I'M CALLING HATTARAS.

19:40.847 --> 19:42.715
YOU'RE OUT OF HERE.
DAD --

19:42.749 --> 19:44.817
"GOT IT UNDER CONTROL"
MY FUCKING ASS.

19:44.851 --> 19:48.488
WELL, TELL THE GOOD DOCTOR,
"HELLO, CHEERIO, PIP-PIP,

19:48.521 --> 19:50.423
AND TAKE THE LIFT."

19:50.457 --> 19:52.892
MAX, HATTARAS
ISN'T SEEING TARA ANYMORE.

19:52.925 --> 19:56.329
BRYCE TRIED TO POISON HIM
WITH CRAB.

19:56.363 --> 19:57.730
POISON HIM?

19:57.764 --> 20:00.967
YEAH, AND HE LIVED.
FUCKER COULDN'T TAKE A JOKE.

20:01.000 --> 20:03.570
WELL, WHO'S LOOKING OUT
FOR TARA?

20:03.603 --> 20:04.771
NO ONE?

20:04.804 --> 20:06.906
T-THERE'S
NO FUCKING NET?!

20:06.939 --> 20:09.309
W-WHAT AM I
SUPPOSED TO DO NOW?

20:09.342 --> 20:10.910
WHAT WERE YOU
GOING TO DO?

20:10.943 --> 20:11.911
I SHOULD GO.

20:11.944 --> 20:13.846
YEAH.
UH, US TOO.

20:13.880 --> 20:15.415
YOU CAN'T LEAVE.

20:15.448 --> 20:17.817
IT'S A PARTY.
DON'T YOU WANT TO PARTY?

20:17.850 --> 20:19.852
OR YOU GOT TO GET BACK
TO THE BABY, HUH?

20:19.886 --> 20:21.688
YES.

20:21.721 --> 20:24.023
ADORABLE LITTLE GIRL
YOU'VE GOT THERE.

20:24.056 --> 20:25.658
JUST AN ANGEL.

20:25.692 --> 20:29.462
YEAH, WE HAD A HELL OF A TIME
WHILE YOU WERE AWAY.

20:29.496 --> 20:32.799
YOU KNOW, NO ONE
TAKES THE BUS ANYMORE

20:32.832 --> 20:36.002
BUT FAT PEOPLE
AND OLD FOLKS...

20:36.035 --> 20:39.539
AND YOUR SWEET,
LITTLE BABY GIRL.

20:39.572 --> 20:44.010
* THE WHEELS ON THE BUS
WITH WHEELS AND BRYCE *

20:44.043 --> 20:45.612
* WHEELS AND BRYCE

20:45.645 --> 20:48.281
* ALL THROUGH THE TOWN

20:48.315 --> 20:49.782
YOU KNEW ABOUT THAT,
RIGHT?

20:49.816 --> 20:51.618
WHAT THE FUCK IS
SHE TALKING ABOUT, CHARMAINE?

20:51.651 --> 20:52.952
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT SHE'S TALKING ABOUT.

20:52.985 --> 20:54.821
IF I FIND OUT --
IF I FIND OUT...

20:54.854 --> 20:56.456
HEY.

20:56.489 --> 20:58.858
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]
WHOA, BUDDY.

20:58.891 --> 21:01.428
WHO ARE YOU DEFENDING, DAD?!
WHO ARE YOU PROTECTING?!

21:01.461 --> 21:02.629
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:02.662 --> 21:04.631
YEAH,
WHOI PROTECTING?

21:04.664 --> 21:06.633
STAY AWAY.

21:06.666 --> 21:08.368
[ TELEPHONE CLATTERS ]
LEAVE OUR FAMILY ALONE.

21:08.401 --> 21:09.569
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:11.338 --> 21:12.572
Kate: I WISH WE WERE
THE SORT OF PEOPLE

21:12.605 --> 21:15.375
WHO COULD JUST GET UPSET
ABOUT ONE THING.

21:15.408 --> 21:17.944
WHEN SOMETHING HAPPENS,
EVERYTHING ELSE SHOULD GO AWAY.

21:17.977 --> 21:21.047
ONE TERRIBLE, HORRIBLE THING
A DAY.

21:21.080 --> 21:23.416
YEAH. I DON'T EXPECT
ANYTHING ELSE.

21:23.450 --> 21:25.818
SHE CAN'T COPE.
HOW CAN SHE HELP ME COPE?

21:25.852 --> 21:27.887
WELL, I DON'T KNOW
IF IT MAKES YOU FEEL ANY BETTER,

21:27.920 --> 21:29.489
BUT IF MOM KNEW
WHAT SHE WAS DOING,

21:29.522 --> 21:31.023
IT WOULD ABSOLUTELY
DESTROY HER.

21:31.057 --> 21:33.793
DOES IT MATTER WHAT SHE THINKS
IF SHE DOES WHAT SHE DOES?

21:33.826 --> 21:35.362
I DON'T KNOW.

21:35.395 --> 21:37.330
YOU'VE GOT TO GET OUT
OF THIS HOUSE.

21:37.364 --> 21:38.698
PLEASE, PROMISE ME.

21:40.567 --> 21:42.835
I ABSOLUTELY WILL.
I PROMISE.

21:42.869 --> 21:44.804
NO. YOU WON'T.

21:44.837 --> 21:47.674
BECAUSE I ALWAYS SAY I'M GONNA
GET OUT OF HERE TOMORROW,

21:47.707 --> 21:50.109
AND I EVEN GET ON A PLANE
EVERY DAY.

21:50.142 --> 21:51.578
I'M STILL HERE.

21:53.713 --> 21:55.682
WHAT DO YOU
EXPECT ME TO DO?

21:55.715 --> 21:58.551
NOTHING. NOTHING.
NO CONTACT.

21:58.585 --> 22:03.089
NO PHONE CALLS,
NO...MULTILAYERED PASTA DISHES.

22:03.122 --> 22:04.991
BUT SHE'S MY SISTER.

22:05.024 --> 22:08.528
AREN'T YOU THE ONE WHO'S
MR. "IT'S ALWAYS ABOUT FAMILY"?

22:08.561 --> 22:10.062
WE'RE YOUR FAMILY.

22:10.096 --> 22:13.366
WE'RE YOUR FAMILY,
NUMBER ONE AND ONLY, ALL RIGHT?

22:13.400 --> 22:17.103
INDIVISIBLE, WITH LIBERTY
AND JUSTICE FOR ALL.

22:17.136 --> 22:18.905
BUT HOW WILL I KNOW
TARA'S OKAY?

22:18.938 --> 22:20.840
YOU DON'T HAVE TO.

22:20.873 --> 22:23.810
SHE'S NOT, ALL RIGHT?
SHE'S NOT OKAY. I WISH SHE WAS.

22:23.843 --> 22:27.980
BUT MY GIRLS HAVE GOT TO BE
OKAY FIRST.

22:28.014 --> 22:30.149
ALL RIGHT?

22:30.182 --> 22:31.718
THAT...

22:31.751 --> 22:34.987
PERSON TOOK OUR BABY.

22:35.021 --> 22:37.824
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

22:37.857 --> 22:41.828
NO ONE IS EVER
GOING TO HURT YOU.

22:41.861 --> 22:42.962
OHH.

22:42.995 --> 22:45.932
[ Breathing heavily ]
SORRY.

22:45.965 --> 22:47.867
HEY. IT'S MY DAY OFF,
AND MY BROTHER'S --

22:47.900 --> 22:49.602
HEY, HEY,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

22:49.636 --> 22:50.937
IT'S HARD.
IT'S REALLY HARD.

22:50.970 --> 22:53.606
AND, UH -- HANG ON.

22:53.640 --> 22:55.608
OKAY,
HERE'S THE THING.

22:55.642 --> 22:57.710
I'M TIRED OF USING MY MOM
AS AN EXCUSE

22:57.744 --> 22:59.979
FOR ALL OF THE CRAP
THAT I CAN'T DEAL WITH,

23:00.012 --> 23:02.982
AND I AM SICK OF ACTING LIKE
HER PROBLEMS ARE MY PROBLEMS.

23:03.015 --> 23:05.151
I WANT TO MAKE
MY OWN PROBLEMS.

23:05.184 --> 23:07.186
THAT'S MY RIGHT
AS A HUMAN FUCKING BEING.

23:07.219 --> 23:09.756
AND SO I CHOOSE YOU.

23:11.758 --> 23:13.793
BE MY PROBLEM.

23:13.826 --> 23:15.862
PLEASE?

23:15.895 --> 23:17.830
OKAY.

23:17.864 --> 23:20.099
DOES THIS MEAN
WE'RE NO LONGER JORTS?

23:20.132 --> 23:21.501
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:21.534 --> 23:23.770
NO. WE'RE CULOTTES.

23:29.041 --> 23:30.910
IT'S ON STANDBY,
I PROMISE.

23:30.943 --> 23:32.812
I KNOW YOUR TRICKS,
GREGSON.

23:32.845 --> 23:34.747
WE JUST NEED A MOMENT.

23:34.781 --> 23:37.049
PRETEND IT WAS JUST BEFORE.
FUTURE LIONEL.

23:37.083 --> 23:39.051
FINE.

23:39.085 --> 23:43.923
IN 10 YEARS, I'M GOING TO LIVE
IN A MANSION IN NEW YORK --

23:43.956 --> 23:48.661
MARBLE FLOORS, POOL BOYS,
FAMOUS FOR BEING FAMOUS.

23:48.695 --> 23:50.497
POOL BOYS IN NEW YORK?

23:50.530 --> 23:53.533
YOU'LL GO TO MANHATTAN,
I'LL GO TO MANHATTAN.

23:53.566 --> 23:56.002
YOUR MANHATTAN
WILL BE IN NEW YORK,

23:56.035 --> 23:58.538
AND MINE WILL BE
AT KANSAS STATE

23:58.571 --> 24:00.707
IN MANHATTAN, KANSAS.

24:00.740 --> 24:03.042
MAYBE IF I WANT
THE MARBLE FLOORS ENOUGH,

24:03.075 --> 24:06.078
I'LL END UP
SOMEPLACE IN THE MIDDLE.

24:06.112 --> 24:08.515
YOU DON'T DREAM
ABOUT ANY REAL THINGS?

24:08.548 --> 24:10.082
[ DOOR OPENS ]

24:10.116 --> 24:12.485
REALITY STAR
CUM MOVIE STAR --

24:12.519 --> 24:13.920
[ TV SHUTS OFF ]

24:13.953 --> 24:16.489
THERE IS A FLOOD OF SHIT
COMING DOWN THE MOUNTAIN.

24:16.523 --> 24:18.090
I NEED SOME MEN
WITH BUCKETS.

24:19.759 --> 24:21.761
MY BUCKET'S
ALMOST FULL.

24:23.863 --> 24:28.100
I THINK I-IT'S BEST FOR EVERYONE
THAT I NOT HANG AROUND.

24:29.736 --> 24:32.972
THEN I...
HEREBY WITHDRAW YOUR BUCKET.

24:33.005 --> 24:35.041
I'LL -- I'LL HOLD 'EM
FOR BOTH OF US.

24:38.010 --> 24:41.213
WHEN YOU GO, I WANT YOU
TO DO SOMETHING FOR ME.

24:41.247 --> 24:43.950
WHEN YOU RAN AROUND NEW YORK,
YOU ACTED LIKE

24:43.983 --> 24:48.955
YOU'D NEVER SEEN A FUCKING
BUILDING OR A BAGEL BEFORE.

24:48.988 --> 24:50.790
DON'T EVER LOSE THAT.

24:53.025 --> 24:55.261
DON'T GIVE THAT UP
FOR HIM.

24:55.294 --> 24:56.863
[ BANG, GLASS SHATTERS ]

24:56.896 --> 24:59.566
OR HER.

24:59.599 --> 25:01.200
IS SHE GONNA BE OKAY?

25:02.935 --> 25:05.204
THAT'S NOT YOUR PROBLEM
ANYMORE.

25:06.739 --> 25:08.007
ARE YOU GONNA BE OKAY?

25:09.742 --> 25:11.544
[ CRASH ]

25:11.578 --> 25:13.112
YOU EVEN...

25:13.145 --> 25:15.147
YOU EVEN KNOW
WHERE YOU'RE GOING?

25:15.181 --> 25:16.983
YEAH.

25:18.150 --> 25:19.786
COME HERE.

25:22.789 --> 25:24.957
YOU CALL ME
WHEN YOU GET THERE.

25:24.991 --> 25:26.826
[ THUMPING ]

25:26.859 --> 25:27.927
[ SNIFFLES ]

25:37.670 --> 25:39.171
YOU WANT ME TO STOP?

25:39.205 --> 25:40.239
YEAH.

25:40.272 --> 25:42.174
FUCK YOU, OLD MAN.

25:42.208 --> 25:44.043
DON'T TELL ME
WHAT TO DO.

25:44.076 --> 25:46.012
WHEN'S TARA COMING BACK?

25:51.350 --> 25:53.285
DON'T YOU GET IT?

25:53.319 --> 25:54.921
[ LAUGHS ]

25:54.954 --> 25:57.056
SHE'S NOT.

25:57.089 --> 26:00.026
